post_text: iLearn Institute at Lenoir City Schools Opening Fall 2018 - We are excited to announce the opening of the iLearn Institute at Lenoir City Schools! Through this entirely new program, traditional home-based learners can earn their diploma entirely through virtual course content delivered by Lenoir City Schools at no cost to the family. Through our hybrid homeschool option, students can attend select classes at Lenoir City High School while still earning the majority of their credits online. If you are a student or parent living in Loudon County who currently homeschools, or who is interested in hearing more about this opportunity, contact Dr. Chris Smallen at 865-988-1934 or c@lenoircityschools.net. http://edne.tw/n512660

Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) program. - Under the new P-EBT program, families of children who receive free or reduced meals at school or
attend a Community Eligibility Provision school may receive financial assistance to replace school
meals during the months of March, April and May due to COVID-19 school closures. The program
will provide parents with $5.70 per child for each day that child qualifies for P-EBT. Click the article title for more information and find out how to apply. http://edne.tw/n644459

post_text: Lenoir City Schools Partners with Footsteps2Brilliance to Provide Community with Literacy App - We are thrilled to let you know that you and your children now have access to the award-winning Footsteps2Brilliance early literacy program. It's a fun pre-K through 3rd grade literacy app with thousands of books, songs, games, and writing activities in English and Spanish. Parents of students in Grades PK-3 can now register for their account at www.myf2b.com/register/lenoir90. Once you resister you can download the app on your phone and play and learn for 15 minutes a day. For more information please click on the title of this article. http://edne.tw/n633210
text: Lenoir City Schools Partners with Footsteps2Brilliance to Provide Community with Literacy App - We are thrilled to let you know that you and your children now have access to the award-winning Footsteps2Brilliance early literacy program. Parents of students in Grades PK-3 can now register for their account at www.myf2b.com/register/lenoir90. Once you resister you can download the app on your phone and play and learn for 15 minutes a day. For more information please click on the title of this article. http://edne.tw/n633210
